{"resourceType":"StructureDefinition","id":"zib-BodyHeight","url":"http://nictiz.nl/fhir/StructureDefinition/zib-BodyHeight","version":"2.1.0","name":"Zib BodyHeight","title":"HCIM BodyHeight","status":"active","publisher":"Nictiz","contact":[{"name":"Nictiz","telecom":[{"system":"email","value":"info@nictiz.nl","use":"work"}]}],"description":"This profile is derived from the HL7 Vital Signs profile for BodyLenght in order to add mappings from the Dutch Health and Care Information models (Dutch: Zorginformatiebouwsteen or ZIB) BodyHeight v3.1, release 2017, and to provide extensions for missing concepts.","purpose":"Body height is used for various reasons, including to measure growth, such as in babies, children or adolescents, to calculate body surface area, to for example calculate the correct amount of medication, or in combination with body weight to calculate the Body Mass Index. Height is also used to determine a person’s nutritional state.","copyright":"CC0","fhirVersion":"3.0.1","mapping":[{"identity":"hcim-bodyheight-v1.2-2015EN","uri":"https://zibs.nl/wiki/BodyHeight-v1.2(2015EN)","name":"HCIM BodyHeight-v1.2(2015EN)"},{"identity":"hcim-bodyheight-v3.0-2016EN","uri":"https://zibs.nl/wiki/BodyHeight-v3.0(2016EN)","name":"HCIM BodyHeight-v3.0(2016EN)"},{"identity":"hcim-bodyheight-v3.1-2017EN","uri":"https://zibs.nl/wiki/BodyHeight-v3.1(2017EN)","name":"HCIM BodyHeight-v3.1(2017EN)"},{"identity":"hcim-basicelements-v1.0-2017EN","uri":"https://zibs.nl/wiki/BasicElements-v1.0(2017EN)","name":"HCIM BasicElements-v1.0(2017EN)"}],"kind":"resource","abstract":false,"type":"Observation","baseDefinition":"http://nictiz.nl/fhir/StructureDefinition/bodyheight","derivation":"constraint","differential":{"element":[{"id":"Observation","path":"Observation","short":"BodyHeight","definition":"The FHIR BodyHeight profile sets a minimum expectations for the Observation Resource to record, search and fetch the body height associated with a patient.","alias":["Lichaamslengte"],